how can i get my dogs to stop barking when someone comes to the door i have pomeranians and when someone comes to the door they all start barking and its really annoying and embarassing how can i get them to stop your dogs are alerting you and each other to the presence of a potentially dangerous intruder alternatively they are very happy to see someone new one becomes excited and they all go crazy i am assuming that you don't have a problem with them barking an alarm but want them to stop barking when you tell them to i would acknowledge that they are doing their job stay very calm and nonchalant yawn a bit shuffle your feet keep your hands down walk slowly etc and praise them for what they are doing then tell them that it is ok and to 'hush' or 'be quiet ' if they continue to bark after that i would tell them again stare at them and be very serious dogs bark naturally but they have to be taught what to bark at they can be taught to bark at the initial sound but to stop barking once you have told them to be quiet it should be a win win situation you have dogs that alert you and they get to do a useful job it takes awhile but eventually they will get into this new habit your job is probably harder because their pack mentality gets them all riled up once one is excited Shaggy dog story Dog training Dog Housebreaking G-Man (Half-Life) The Death Gate Cycle Carl Barks Social rule Late Night with Conan O'Brien Milton H. Erickson The Price Is Right Skinny Puppy Futurama (TV series - season 5) Obedience training Toilet humour The Lion, the Witch and the Wardrobe Reservoir Dogs Harry Potter and the Prisoner of Azkaban Pomeranian (dog) Garfield Russian joke Harry Potter and the Order of the Phoenix The Time Machine The Shining (film) Kodocha Shetland Sheepdog Police dog Humphrey Bogart Knots Landing Episodes of Lost (Season 1) Hiking Hansel und Gretel Don Rosa The Apprentice 2 Out of Gas Series finale Combine (Half-Life 2) Haven (TNG episode) Monty Hall problem Men in Black 